Package util.searchable

Interface ISearchableByFilter<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the expected result Collection
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ITree<TREETYPE>, ITreeNode<NODETYPE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CategoryTreeNode, Container, CopyableTreeNode, GenericTree, GenericTreeNode, ProductCategoryTreeNode, ProductTree, ProductTreeNode
    public interface ISearchableByFilter<T>
    This interfaces defines behavior that allows to filter an object with an ISearchFilter. Each class that implements this interface has to provide an implementation for searchByFilter(ISearchFilter, Object). The actual filter function ISearchFilter (how the object is compared to a passed object) is passed along as an argument.
    Author:
    OOP

    • Method Detail

      • searchByFilter

        Collection<T> searchByFilter​(ISearchFilter filter,
                             Object compareObject)
        All implementations of this interface allow searching for one or many matching objects in its context using ISearchFilter.searchFilterFunction(Object, Object).

        The filter is applied on features, determined by the implementing class, and evaluates if it matches the passed compare object. Each matching feature is added to a Collection and returned.

        Parameters:
        filter - the ISearchFilter used to search
        compareObject - the object that is used for comparison
        Returns:
        a Collection of objects matching the filter function
